<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yangtze Flood Crest Passes Southwest China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, August 23 (Xinhua) -- A major flood peak of the
Yangtze River's upper reaches passed the Cuntan Measuring Point at
Chongqing Municipality in southwest China on Sunday at 16 pm.
</P>
<P>
The water level reached 183.21 meters and had a flow rate of
58,000 cubic meters, 1.1 meters higher and 3,100 cubic meters more
than the figures of the previous flood crest.
</P>
<P>
The new flood peak in the upper reaches of the Yangtze could
bring more difficulties to flood-fighting in downstream areas,
according to local officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
