<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Names Chernomyrdin Interim Premier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
abruptly dismissed the entire Russian government on Sunday as
Prime Minister Sergei Kiriyenko and his cabinet was unable to
solve the economic and financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
In a statement released by the Kremlin, Yeltsin said he had
signed a decree sacking the government and naming former prime
minister Viktor Chernomyrdin, 60, as interim prime minister.
</P>
<P>
The presidential decree said "the government of the Russian
Federation has resigned."
</P>
<P>
The decree, which took immediate effect, said that "the interim
head of the government will be Viktor Stepanovich Chernomyrdin."
</P>
<P>
It was the second time Yeltsin has sacked his entire government
this year. He dismissed Chernomyrdin, 60, and his cabinet on March
23.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin served as prime minister for more than five years
until March. He won a reputation as a solid but unspectacular
reformer, and announced plans to run in the next presidential
election shortly after he was dismissed in March.
</P>
<P>
Interfax news agency said Chernomyrdin was holding
consultations on creating a new cabinet.
</P>
<P>
After the Kremlin announced the cabinet dismissal, State Duma
Speaker Gennady Seleznyov immediately welcomed Chernomyrdin's
appointment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
