<HEADLINE> Nigerian Top Leader Visits S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's military ruler,
General Abdusalam Abubakar, arrived in Pretoria Sunday afternoon
at the start of a three-day visit to South Africa.
</P>
<P>
He was met at the airport by Deputy President Thabo Mbeki and
Foreign Minister Alfred Nzo.
</P>
<P>
It is Abubakar's first visit abroad since he took state power of
Nigeria on June 9.
</P>
<P>
South African Press Association quoted unidentified officials as
saying that Abubakar will hold talks with President Nelson Mandela
in Pretoria on Monday and Mbeki in Cape Town on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Abubakar will brief South African
parliament members on his plan to democratize Nigeria. In addition,
the conflict in the Democratic Republic of the Congo will also be
discussed, the officials said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
