<DOCNO> XIE19980824.0010 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Grabs First-ever Away Point against Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai Shenhua grabbed their
first-ever away point against Beijing in the league history after
they managed a 1-1 draw with Beijing Guo'an in the Chinese first
division soccer league on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai, who came here without even managing a tie away
against Guo'an since the league began in 1994, opened the scoring
through Paraguyan Sando Valg Elvio.
</P>
<P>
Elvio beat several defenders and the goalie before chipping
the ball into the empty net just seconds before the break.
</P>
<P>
The home team stormed back in the second half and their
efforts were paid off when Olivas Rubio Andres of Spain headed in
the equalizer on Wang Shaolei's cross in the 68th minute.
</P>
<P>
The previous four encounters between the two sides here all
ended with Beijing winning, mostly with a large margin. Last
season Beijing won 9-1.
</P>
<P>
In Qingdao, Shandong Province, defending champions Dalian
Wanda proved the class of their own as they thrashed the Qingdao
Hainiu 3-1.
</P>
<P>
Hao Haidong scored twice and Sun Jihai added another to make
it 3-0 with 25 minutes left in the game before Cao Xiandong
scored a consoling goal for Hainiu in the remaining time.
</P>
<P>
Wuhan Hongjinlong extended their home win streak to three
games as the team, under the guidance of the new head coach Qi
Wusheng, defeated Sichuan Quanxing 2-1.
</P>
<P>
But it was the visitors who found the net first as Liu Bin
scored a 25th-minute goal after Wei Qun's powerful shot hit the
post and landed into Liu's path.
</P>
<P>
Wuhan then scored twice in an expanse of just three minutes
from 85th to 87th minutes to grab the three points.
</P>
<P>
There is little change on the overall standings, with the top
six places remaining the same as those of last round.
</P>
<P>
In the other games Sunday, Chinese Army beat Guangzhou Apollo
2-1, Guangzhou Songri defeated Yanbian Aodong 2-1, Shenzhen edged
Shandong 4-3 while Vanguards drew with Shenyang 2-2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
