<HEADLINE> Kuwait Says it Rejects All Forms of Terrorism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait said Sunday it
rejects all forms of terrorism and calls on the international
community to take effective measures to combat terrorist acts.
</P>
<P>
The Kuwaiti government made the statement at a weekly cabinet
meeting, the official news agency KUNA reported.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait has been following up with great concern the recent
terrorist events that caused casualties and property damage, the
agency quoted government officials as saying.
</P>
<P>
The statement stressed the need to intensify all common efforts
to spare the international community from further losses, and
cement international stability and security for all nations.
</P>
<P>
The statement came after the U.S. launched missile attacks
thursday evening on what it described as "terrorist-related"
targets in Sudan and Afghanistan following the twin bombings of
the U.S. embassies in Kenya and Tanzania, which killed more than
260 people, including 12 Americans.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait is one of several Arab states in which the U.S. troops
are stationed. 
