an effort to advance the peace process, and not to deal in
ceremonialism and nostalgia.
</P>
<P>
Parliament coalition chairman Meir Sheetrit and Netanyahu's
political advisor Uzi Arad were sent by Netanyahu to represent
the Israeli government at the event in Oslo. The two left for Oslo
on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Former Israeli Prime Minister Shimon Peres, who will attend
the Oslo functions together with U.S. Middle East peace envoy
Dennis Ross, said last weekend that "it is a terrible mistake"
that Netanyahu refused to turn up.
</P>
<P>
"We owned our thanks to the people of Norway," Peres said.
</P>
