<HEADLINE> India's FCA Falls Further </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 24 (Xinhua) -- India's foreign currency
assets (FCA) fell by over 500 million U.S. dollars to 23,538
million dollars during the week ended August 14, said the Reserve
Bank of India's weekly statistical supplement Monday.
</P>
<P>
With special drawing rights dwindling by 17 million dollars,
the country's total foreign exchange reserves were 519 million
dollars lower at 26,608 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Fall in FCA since end-March, 1998 has been 2,437 million
dollars. 
