<HEADLINE> Russian Duma to Discuss Nomination of PM in 10 Days </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 24 (Xinhua) -- The Russian State Duma, the
lower house of the parliament, will discuss the nomination of
Viktor Chernomyrdin as prime minister in 10 days instead of the
seven days stipulated by legislation.
</P>
<P>
The Itar-Tass news agency quoted Duma Speaker Gennady Seleznyov
as saying Monday that the Duma needed at least 10 days prepare a
meeting on confirmation of the nomination.
</P>
<P>
After holding a telephone conversation with President Boris
Yeltsin on Monday, Seleznyov said Yeltsin had agreed to postpone
the discussion of the candidacy of Chernomyrdin for prime minister.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin was nominated as acting prime minister by Yeltsin
following the sacking of the entire government headed by Sergei
Kiriyenko on Sunday. In a letter to the Duma later, Yeltsin
nominated Chernomyrdin as the prime minister and gave him a clear
mandate to reorganize the government and formulate its programs.
</P>
<P>
Earlier on Monday, the Duma Council called on Yeltsin to
withdraw his letter concerning the candidacy of Chernomyrdin.
</P>
<P>
Seleznyov said that Yeltsin was ready to put a different date
on his letter to the Duma on Chernomyrdin's nomination.
</P>
<P>
He said that he stood for creating a trilateral commission on
the formation of a new government and preparation of its programs.
</P>
<P>
Such a commission would include representatives of the
government, the Federation Council and the State Duma, he noted.
</P>
</TEXT>
