<DOCNO> XIE19980824.0059 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rehabilitation Conference Discusses Employment of Disabled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Delegates to the 11th
Rehabilitation International Asia and the Pacific Regional
Conference focused their discussions on a series of issues
including employment of the disabled here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The conference cum Campaign'98 for the Asian and Pacific Decade
of Disabled Persons 1993-2002, which opened here Sunday, is
attended by 700 local delegates, 300 overseas delegates from about
50 countries and 350 delegates from the Chinese mainland.
</P>
<P>
Gabriele Stoikov, chief of the vocational Rehabilitation Branch
of the International Labor Office, delivered a speech on global
perspectives on employment of persons with disabilities.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the environment in which employment opportunities
for people with disabilities have been developing and expanding
has undergone dramatic changes in the past decades.
</P>
<P>
Not all the changes are happening in every country, and where
changes happen, the impact differs, depending on a range of
social, economic, cultural, political and historical factors, he
said.
</P>
<P>
In his view, he said that the issues including job retention,
return to work and employment creation policies are of prime
importance for persons with disabilities in the labor market.
</P>
<P>
Liu Xincheng, representative from the Chinese Ministry of Labor
and Social Security, briefed the participants on employment of the
disabled in China which is regarded as a very important component
of the country's employment work.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1997, he said that local governments promulgated
regulations on proportionate employment of the disabled,
and the set proportion for the employment of the disabled was
between 1.5 and 2 percent.
</P>
<P>
During the Eighth Five-Year Plan period (1991-1995), a total of
680,000 disabled people were employed in urban areas and the
employment rate of the urban disabled increased from 51 percent to
67 percent.
</P>
<P>
In rural areas, he said over 2 million handicapped persons are
taking part in different forms of production activities, 60,000
disabled are employed in township or village-run enterprises and
500,000 disabled have received practical skills training through
carrying out poverty-relief program.
</P>
<P>
The targets for the employment of the disabled during the Ninth
Five-year Plan (1996-2000) are: the employment rate of the
disabled will reach about 80 percent, providing employment to
600,000 disabled in urban areas and further increasing the
employment level of the disabled in rural areas by 2000, he said.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from Hong Kong and countries including India,
Britain also delivered speeches during Monday's meeting.
</P>
<P>
Their topics ranged from early intervention in low income
communities, meeting the challenge of intellectual disabilities,
to methods of resourcing long-term care for senior citizens with a
disability. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
