<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Algeria Denies Military Nuclear Program Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Algeria Monday denied a report
that it is developing a nuclear program which will allow it to
produce military grade plutonium.
</P>
<P>
Algerian Foreign Ministry spokesman Abdelzziz Sebaa said that
the "allegations" by Spanish newspaper El Pais, which quoted
Spanish intelligence sources that Algiers was developing such a
nuclear program, were "unhealthy and sensational".
</P>
<P>
"Algeria is a signatory country of the Non-Proliferation Treaty
and has an agreement with the International Atomic Energy Agency
with which it maintains a cooperation of quality," said the
spokesman.
</P>
<P>
He said that Algeria's nuclear program had only peaceful
purposes aimed at economic and social development.
</P>
<P>
El Pais quoted the Spanish Superior Center of Information of
Defense as saying, "The Algerian nuclear program continues to
provide itself with necessary installations for realizing all the
operations linked with the obtaining of plutonium of military
type, the key element for a nuclear program." 
</P>
</TEXT>
