<HEADLINE> Indian Defense College Team Visits Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 24 (Xinhua) -- An 18-member team from the
National Defense College of India Monday began a four-day visit to
Nepal, the Indian Embassy in Kathmandu said.
</P>
<P>
The team, which has officers from Sri Lanka, St. Helena, Syria
and Nigeria as well, will exchange views with senior Nepalese
civil and military officials and call on Prime Minister Girija
Prasad Koirala and other senior government officials, the embassy
said in a press release.
</P>
<P>
The college is an apex institution in India in the study of the
higher direction of policy at the national and international level
and the course is attended by senior officers of the Indian
defense forces and civil services as well as armed forces officers
of friendly foreign countries, the embassy said.
</P>
<P>
It noted that at present, Brig. General Bala Nanda Sharma of
Nepal is attending the course.
</P>
<P>
"As part of their curriculum, the college organizes tours to
neighboring and other foreign countries to enable student officers
to interact with their counterparts and acquaint themselves with
the socio-political, economic, defense and foreign policy aspects
of the countries they visit," it said. 
