<HEADLINE> China's NPC Standing Committee Studying Drafts Of Five Laws </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 24 (Xinhua) -- China's highest legislative body
plans to discuss a draft of the first contract law and amendments
to the adoption law.
</P>
<P>
The proposed contracts law will combine three existing laws,
parts of which contradict each other in some ways, according to Hu
Kangsheng, deputy-director of the Commission of the Legislative
Affairs of the National People's Congress (NPC).
</P>
<P>
The amendments to the adoption law require stricter
qualifications for foreigners adopting Chinese children and
greater safety for adopted children.
</P>
<P>
Drafts of a higher education law, amendments to the Land-Use
Law, and organization of village committees law are still being
discussed. Qiao Xiaoyang, Li Boyong and Zhou Keyu, who are
vice-chairmen of the NPC Law Committee, explained the latest
drafts this morning.
</P>
<P>
The NPC Standing Committee published copies of the amendments
to the Land-Use Law and organization of village committees law for
the public to discuss.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Lilan, the Minister of Science and Technology, explained a
proposal for an international treaty protecting various plants and
Zhang Deguang, the Vice-Minister of Foreign Affairs, explained a
proposal on two protocols on the Convention on Certain
Conventional Weapons.
</P>
<P>
Zou Jiahua, Vice-Chairman of the NPC Standing Committee,
reported on law enforcement of marine environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, Chairman of the NPC Standing Committee, presided over
the inaugural meeting of the fourth meeting of the Ninth NPC
Standing Committee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
