<HEADLINE> Supplies For Flooded Areas Called for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Premier Zhu Rongji says he is
concerned about relief supplies, especially clothing and shelter,
for flood-stricken parts of northeastern China.
</P>
<P>
The premier has told various central departments to deliver the
goods as soon and as efficiently as possible.
</P>
<P>
Heilongjiang and Jilin provinces and the Inner Mongolia
Autonomous Region have been battling severe flooding for the past
several weeks.
</P>
<P>
The State Flood Control and Drought Relief Headquarters, with
help from the army, is delivering 13,450 tents, 20,000 life vests,
and cotton-padded garments to flood victims and troops.
</P>
<P>
Authorities have told tent manufacturers to increase
production. Officials say that the manufacturers could produce
50,000 tents a month and that that could meet the demand. 
</P>
