<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice Premier's Encouraging Words For Young Scientists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Li Lanqing told a
group of young Chinese scientists that the government should trust
and support young scientists to help them concentrate on their
academic research and technological development.
</P>
<P>
Li told the young scientists, who were attending the Third
Annual Symposium of Young Scientists, which is sponsored by the
China Association for Science and Technology, that the requisite
conditions and assistance should be available for those who work
abroad but want to help the motherland so that they can serve
China in various ways.
</P>
<P>
Young scientists should devote themselves to the country's
modernization drive and apply the strategy of "invigorating China
with science and technology", Li said, emphasizing the urgent need
for a large number of young professionals to meet the requirements
of the modernization drive for the next century.
</P>
<P>
Over 700 young scientists, who either work at home or abroad,
participated in the symposium in Beijing from August 20 to 22.
</P>
