<HEADLINE> EU Offers Humanitarian Aid to War-Torn Sierra Leone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 24 (Xinhua) -- The European Union has granted
six million European Currency Units (6.6 million U.S. dollars) in
humanitarian aid to Sierra Leone plagued by a seven-year civil war.
</P>
<P>
The European Commission, executive arm of the 15-member bloc,
announced Monday that the aid, to be managed by the European
Community Humanitarian Office, is to help the victims of the west
African conflict.
</P>
<P>
Commission officials said that non-governmental organizations
would use the funds to carry out aid programs that would also
reach refugees in Guinea and Liberia.
</P>
<P>
An estimated total of 60,000 people are believed to have been
displaced in Sierra Leone, while 150,000 others are thought to
have fled to neighboring Guinea and another 50,000 to Liberia.
</P>
<P>
The funds will mainly cover health and food aid for refugees.
</P>
