<HEADLINE> Russian Ruble Down 1350 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MOSCOW, August 24 (Xinhua) -- The Russian ruble fell 1350
points (13.5 kopecks) against the U.S. dollar on Monday after
President Boris Yeltsin's dismissal of the entire government on
Sunday, the Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The official ruble exchange rate was fixed at 7.1400 to the
dollar at the Moscow Interbank Currency Exchange on Monday morning.
</P>
<P>
The volume of tenders amounted to 227.76 million dollars,
while 115 deals were concluded, dealers said.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin on Sunday sacked Prime Minister Sergei Kiriyenko and
his entire cabinet and named former prime minister Viktor
Chernomyrdin as interim premier.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said the abrupt cabinet dismissal is a real cause of
the ruble's devaluation. 
