<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinhua Interviews Taiwan Affairs Office Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Political negotiations between
the Chinese mainland and Taiwan Province remain high on the
agenda, according to a leading official from the State
Council's Taiwan Affairs Office.
</P>
<P>
Speaking in a recent interview with Xinhua, the official said
that the concerted efforts of Chinese people on both sides of the
Taiwan Straits have led to the steady development of economic and
cultural exchanges in recent years.
</P>
<P>
"We have consistently called for a formal end to the state of
hostilities between the two sides in accordance with the 'one
China' principle and the beginning of talks covering procedural
arrangements for political negotiations, as well as the resumption
of economic and practical negotiations between the Association for
Relations Across the Taiwan Straits (ARATS) and the Taiwan-based
Straits Exchange Foundation (SEF)," according to the official.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan authorities should exhibit their true intent to end
hostilities between the two sides by abandoning their "two Chinas"
stand, said the official, adding that they have no reason to delay
talks on procedural issues involving political negotiations.
</P>
<P>
The official reiterated that the the ARATS welcomes SEF
Chairman Koo Chen-fu and his delegation to visit the mainland in
either September or October.
</P>
<P>
He said, "With the exception of those who stubbornly insist on
the 'independence of Taiwan', we will be delighted to hold talks
with Taiwan residents from various parties and all walks of life
concerning cross-straits relations and China's peaceful
reunification.
</P>
<P>
If Taiwan authorities are truly committed to the reunification
of China, they should steadfastly refrain from creating disputes
over social systems. At the same time, they should abandon
attempts to explore broader international living space and to seek
membership in the United Nations, as well as actions disrupting
exchanges between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the "independence of Taiwan" and "two Chinas"
are beyond the realm of possibility, no matter it's from the point
of view of common wishes of Chinese people on both sides or from
the trend of international situation.
</P>
<P>
He said, "We sincerely hope that Taiwan authorities will
fulfill promises concerning the "one China principle", and will
remove all barriers to promote the great cause of peaceful
reunification."
</P>
<P>
The official asked Chinese citizens on both sides of the Taiwan
Straits to join hands and engage in a concerted effort to ensure
the timely realization of reunification of the motherland and for
the invigoration of the Chinese nation in the 21st century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
