<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Monday.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index lost 6.86
points to 317.20, the all-share Emas Index was down by 1.64 points
to 82.56, the Industrial Index dipped 17.36 points to 652.20 while
the Second Board Index was 1.60 points lower to 78.01.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers by 388 to 134 while 117 counters were
unchanged, 283 counters untraded and 38 suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's total turnover declined to 95.178 million shares
valued at 163.369 million ringgit (about 38.804 million U.S.
dollars) from last Friday's 142.720 million shares valued at
214.508 million ringgit (about 50.952 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
The main board volume declined to 90.752 million shares valued
at 158.929 million ringgit (about 37.75 million dollars) from last
Friday's 135.775 million shares worth 208.192 million ringgit
(about 49.451 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
The second board turnover was lower at 4.426 million shares
worth 4.439 million ringgit (about 1.054 million dollars) from
6.945 million shares valued at 6.316 million ringgit (about 1.5
million dollars) last Friday.
</P>
<P>
Off market transactions increased to 2.205 million shares
valued at 5.894 million ringgit (about 1.4 million dollars) from
last Friday's 1.477 million shares worth 5.340 million ringgit
(about 1.268 million dollars). 
