<HEADLINE> Kohl Voices Trust of Chernomyrdin's Ability to Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 24 (Xinhua) -- German Chancellor Helmut Kohl said
Monday he was confident that Russian Acting Prime Minister Viktor
Chernomyrdin will push through the necessary reforms to stem the
financial crisis in Russia.
</P>
<P>
"The chancellor has stressed that he trusts Chernomyrdin, whom
he and the German government know well and appreciate through many
years of good cooperation," said Kohl's spokesman, Otto Hauser,
Monday morning.
</P>
<P>
"Kohl is confident that Chernomyrdin will push through the
necessary decisions given the dramatic and serious situation in
Russia," the spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
Apparently under the increasing pressure of a financial crisis,
Yeltsin earlier on Sunday suddenly sacked the entire cabinet of
Sergei Kiriyenko and named former Prime Minister Viktor
Chernomyrdin, who was fired just five months ago, as Acting Prime
Minister.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin has asked the Russian State Duma, the lower house of
parliament, to approve Chernomyrdin's nomination, reports said.
</P>
</TEXT>
