<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore President Calls For Close ASEAN Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Singapore President Ong Teng
Cheong Monday called upon ASEAN members to work together in their
efforts to tide over the current regional economic crisis.
</P>
<P>
In his message of greetings to the 19th ASEAN
Inter-Parliamentary Organization (AIPO) General Assembly opened in
the Malaysian capital of Kuala Lumpur Monday, Ong expressed his
belief that by working together and helping one another ASEAN
(Association of Southeast Asian Nations) can overcome its problems
and emerge even stronger although it is now facing a difficult
period in its history.
</P>
<P>
Noting it is not the first time that the region is facing
serious problems, the president said "it is in times like this
that we must rely on our strong network of relations to confront
these challenges."
</P>
<P>
"We must continue to take a pro-active approach to overcome the
current economic turmoil engulfing our respective economies," he
added.
</P>
<P>
He also said ASEAN must continue to keep its economies open in
order to remain relevant in a world of globalized markets and
remain committed to economic liberalization and achieve
integration by fully implementing the AFTA (ASEAN Free Trade
Area).
</P>
<P>
The president also asked the parliamentarians to help keep
ASEAN fundamental principles and goals, to rally support for ASEAN
and promote strong personal ties and network among ASEAN current
and future leaders.
</P>
<P>
AIPO, therefore, is an important platform where ASEAN
cooperation can continue to be nurtured and strengthened, he said.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
