<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Intercepts More Contraband Goods in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 24 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Customs
Authority announced Monday that it has intercepted various
contraband goods worth over 51.6 million Birr (7.37 million U.S.
Dollars) in the 1997/98 fiscal year ending on July 7.
</P>
<P>
The intercepted goods were worth 12 million Birr (1.71 million
U.S. Dollars) over the previous 1996/97 fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
Tesfaye Kibret, representative of the legal department of the
authority, was quoted by Ethiopian News Agency as saying that the
contraband goods intercepted included new and second-hand
clothes, radio and television sets as well as tape recorders and
other electronics equipment.
</P>
<P>
Tesfaye contributed the increase to the newly introduced
monitoring mechanism and the efforts of employees of the
authority.
</P>
<P>
The contraband goods were transported by vehicles, pack
animals and individuals and the main entrance points of them were
the north and north-east parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
There are 33 contraband check points in Ethiopia, according to
the representative. 
</P>
</TEXT>
