<HEADLINE> Nepali Parliament Passes Budget Before Cabinet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 24 (Xinhua) -- The Lower House of Nepali
Parliament Monday passed by a majority the budget for 1998-99
fiscal year which began in mid-July as Prime Minister Girija
Prasad Koirala is expected to reshuffle his cabinet, most probably
on Tuesday, for induction of communists.
</P>
<P>
The ruling Nepali Congress, the single largest party in
parliament said "yes" to the budget, while the main opposition
Communist Party of Nepal (United Marxism-Leninism, CPN-UML), the
minor National Democratic Party (Thapa) and the Nepal Sadbhavana
Party said "no."
</P>
<P>
The 40 MPs of Communist Party of Nepal (Marxism-Leninism,
CPN-ML), which has decided to join the present government,
remained silent in the voice vote.
</P>
<P>
When the parliament voted in early July on the policies and
programs tabled by the government for the new fiscal year, CPN-ML
abstained, ensuring the victory for the government.
</P>
<P>
The next general elections due before November 1999 led to the
alliance between NC and CPN-ML, which will give a comfortable
majority to the coming coalition government.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Koirala, who came to power in mid-April, is
expected to reshuffle the cabinet most probably on Tuesday to
include CPN-ML so as to turn his minority government into a
coalition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
