<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Draft Laws Amended In Response to Public Opinions (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BEIJING, August 24 (Xinhua) - Draft laws on land management
and the organization of village committees have been revised in
response to public opinion, according to a meeting attended by
members of the National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee
which opened today.
</P>
<P>
These are the first two draft laws published by the ninth NPC
Standing Committee to solicit public opinion. The revised drafts
were submitted to the legislature for further discussion today.
</P>
<P>
Fourteen changes were made to the draft law on land management
relating to the issues of building factories on farmland and land
distribution, among many others.
</P>
<P>
In response to letters from the public and advocacy from local
governments and legislators, the new laws increase the local
legislature's role in protecting farmland and supervising the
government's land management.
</P>
<P>
Some farmers wrote to the legislature that tighter controls
should be imposed on farmlands to prevent them from being
commercialized. Thus, a new amendment was added that the use of
farmland for industrial projects must be authorized by the
government.
</P>
</TEXT>
