<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Upper House Speaker Backs Chernomyrdin's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 24 (Xinhua) -- The speaker of Russian upper
house of parliament on Monday expressed his support for President
Boris Yeltsin's nomination of Viktor Chernomyrdin as new prime
minister.
</P>
<P>
"It is a constitutional right of Russian president to appoint
and sack chiefs of cabinet," Yegor Stroyev, speaker of the
Federation Council, said.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin was appointed acting premier after Yeltsin sacked
the entire cabinet of Sergei Kiriyenko Sunday night amid a
serious financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
The new cabinet "should be formed on a basis of accord and
stability in society", Stroyev said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Monday, Yeltsin telephoned speaker of the lower house
of parliament on the establishment of a tripartite conciliation
commission.
</P>
<P>
The conciliation commission, to be composed of the government,
now under Viktor Chernomyrdin, the Duma and the Federation
Council, or upper house of parliament, was to develop an
anti-crisis program, Yeltsin's spokesman Sergei Yastrzhembsky said.
</P>
<P>
Yastrzhembsky quoted Yeltsin as saying that he had authorized
Chernomyrdin to discuss the content of the program and cabinet
line-up on behalf of the executive authority, the Itar-Tass news
agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin's offer of a conciliation commission was believed to be
a gesture of peace to lawmakers, especially hostile deputies of
the opposition factions in the Duma, who only last Friday passed a
resolution urging Yeltsin to step down.
</P>
<P>
News of Chernomyrdin's authority on personnel matters had
emerged earlier Monday. Some reports said that the 60-year-old
Chernomyrdin had set this as a precondition for his return to
government.
</P>
<P>
About five months ago, Chernomyrdin's cabinet was abruptly
fired by Yeltsin.
</P>
<P>
As debate over composition of the new cabinet intensified,
Chernomyrdin held meetings with leaders of various factions of the
State Duma in an effort to rally support.
</P>
<P>
However, Chernomyrdin said he would only announce the new
cabinet line-up after the State Duma approved his nomination of
prime minister.
</P>
<P>
Besides meeting Chernomyrdin Monday afternoon, Yeltsin also
held what was described as "working meetings" with the acting
ministers of defense, interior and the acting head of the Federal
Security Service, the presidential press service said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
