<HEADLINE> Composite Consumer Price Index in Macao Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, August 24 (Xinhua) -- The composite consumer price index
for July in Macao was 102.9, a slight decrease of 0.3 percent over
the previous month, according to figures released by the Census
and Statistics Department of the Macao government Monday.
</P>
<P>
The average prices of clothing, daily necessities, maintenance,
 education and recreation went down, while those of transport,
telecommunications and medical care rose.
</P>
<P>
During the first seven months of the year, the average price
index increased 1.4 percent over the same period last year. But
the index for July decreased 0.7 percent compared with the same
month in 1997. 
