<HEADLINE> Epidemic Disease Prevention in Central China's Flood Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, August 24 (Xinhua) -- While fighting floods, central
China's Hunan Province has put the prevention of epidemic disease
at the top of its important tasks that must be accomplished.
</P>
<P>
Since the middle of this month, the provincial government has
invested a total of 3.5 million yuan to carry out a three-month
disease-prevention program in the flood-stricken areas.
</P>
<P>
Some 1,560 teams of 15,000 doctors and disease prevention
medics have been sent to the flooded areas.
</P>
<P>
Sanitation workers have opened hundreds of clinics and medical
centers in the flood-ravaged villages, townships, counties and
cities. To date, they have distributed drugs to over 1.87 million
flood victims and PLA soldiers.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the provincial government is focusing on providing
disease prevention information and monitoring food, drinking water,
and environmental conditions in order to control summer and
autumn epidemic diseases.  
</P>
