<HEADLINE> China's Electronic Information Products Grow Rapidly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Latest statistics from the
State Statistics Bureau show that in the January-July period the
output of China's electronic information products grew rapidly.
</P>
<P>
During this period, the output of micro-computers increased by 45
percent on a year-to-year basis, while that of mobile telecom
equipment grew by 41 percent, and program-controlled
switchboards were up 34 percent.
</P>
<P>
Experts from the bureau noted this indicates that China has
put the electronic information industry high on the list of its
plans for economic development.
</P>
<P>
In July, the growth rate of switchboard output stood as high as
55 percent.
</P>
<P>
In the first seven months of this year, the output of major raw
material products, such as nonferrous metals, plate glass, and
steel increased to varying degrees, while production of energy
declined to varying decrees.
</P>
<P>
Affected by a slumping market, the output of consumer durables
such as refrigerators and washing machines decreased, the bureau
said. 
</P>
