<HEADLINE> Chernomyrdin Nominated, Shaping Cabinet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Russian Acting Prime Minister
Viktor Chernomyrdin met leaders of various factions in the State
Duma Monday morning in an effort to form a new government.
</P>
<P>
Nomination for his premiership has already been submitted to
the State Duma, or lower house of parliament, by President Boris
Yeltsin.
</P>
<P>
The 60-year-old Chernomyrdin, who replaced Sergei Kiriyenko
only five months after Yeltsin fired him, is expected to face a
hostile Duma in terms of his confirmation.
</P>
<P>
The Communist Party, the largest opposition faction in the
lower house, and the Agrarian and People's Power groups, have
already voiced their opposition.
</P>
<P>
They have asked Yeltsin to withdraw Chernomyrdin's nomination,
Communist leader Gennady Zyuganov told reporters.
</P>
<P>
He again demanded that Yeltsin step down. "As long as Yeltsin
remains in power, no reshuffling will lead the country out of the
crisis."
</P>
<P>
Before accepting Yeltsin's offer, Chernomyrdin had set the
condition that he be given the authority to shape the cabinet's
line-up, the local Ekho Moskvy radio station reported, quoting a
source close to Chernomyrdin.
</P>
<P>
Kiriyenko, barely four months in office, met news of his ouster
Sunday night calmly, thanking his aides and made a telephone call
to U.S. Vice President Al Gore.
</P>
<P>
He had already turned down an offer by Yeltsin to remain in the
government as a first deputy prime minister, the Itar-Tass
reported, quoting a government source.
</P>
<P>
The government shake-up sent the weak ruble to a new low of
7.14 rubles to the U.S. dollar on the Moscow Interbank Currency
Exchange (MICEX).
</P>
<P>
Duma speaker Gennady Seleznyov had predicted "important news"
later Monday.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin, who held closed-door meeting with Chernomyrdin, told
the nation that the move to bring down the Kiriyenko cabinet was
to ensure the stability and normalcy of the Russian people.
</P>
<P>
In a televised address to the nation, Yeltsin said he had
discussed the line-up of the new cabinet with Chernomyrdin.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
