<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Troops Kill 6 Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
Sunday killed six Tamil rebels in the north of the country,
according to a military spokesman Monday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Ink Dewage said government troops confronted a group
of rebels Sunday afternoon in the southeast of Mankulam and
engaged with small arms. Troops confirmed that four rebels were
killed there.
</P>
<P>
In another incident around 5:45 p.m. on the same day northwest
of Kunchikkulam, troops destroyed a terrorist bunker killing two
rebels.
</P>
<P>
During daytime rebels fired mortars at troops south of Vannivi
Lankulam, said the spokesman, adding that the troops retaliated
with mortars and artillery, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a 15-year war against the
government since 1983 for a separate state in the north and east
of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
