<DOCNO> XIE19980824.0180 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tianjin Improves Services for Overseas-Funded Businesses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, August 24 (Xinhua) -- North China's Tianjin
Municipality has engaged in extensive efforts to improve
services to overseas-funded companies and solve related
production problems.
</P>
<P>
The municipality designated the month of June as a month to
assist overseas-funded businesses, with teams organized by various
local government departments solving over 500 problems during
visits to over 1,100 enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin banks granted loans of over 250 million yuan to help 12
overseas-funded enterprises overcome problems related to shortages
of floating capital.
</P>
<P>
The municipality not only reduced levies of miscellaneous fees,
but also introduced a range of new preferential policies to
encourage overseas investors to enter key sectors.
</P>
<P>
Improved services have sparked a rapid flow of overseas
investment to the largest port city of north China.
</P>
<P>
The Municipal Foreign Trade and Economic Commission
released figures showing the city approved 563 overseas-funded
projects in the first seven months of the year, up five on the
same period last year. Contracted overseas investment for the
period hit 2.12 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Allocated overseas investment approached 1.38 billion
U.S. dollars, a level close to the 1997 period.
</P>
<P>
The municipality's 11,000 overseas-funded enterprises account
for a third of the local economic strength.  
</P>
</TEXT>
