<HEADLINE> 11 Kurdish Rebels Killed in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Eleven rebels of the outlawed
Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) were killed Monday in clashes with
Turkish security forces in southeastern Turkey, the semi-official
Anatolia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The agency said the security forces on duty exchanged fire with
PKK fighters at the Satira Tepe region in Kozluk town of Batman
province late Sunday night, and the fighting lasted till early
Monday morning, leaving 11 PKK militants dead.
</P>
<P>
It did not disclose whether there were any casualties among the
government troops during the clashes with the PKK.
</P>
<P>
Over 35,000 people have been killed in the conflicts since the
PKK started a separatist war for autonomy in southeastern Turkey
in August 1984. 
