<HEADLINE> New Zealand Sees More Visitors in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, August 24 (Xinhua) -- There were 106,540 visitor
arrivals in New Zealand in July, one percent more than in the same
month of last year, according to government statistics released
here Monday.
</P>
<P>
But for the whole year ending on July 1998, 1.459 million
people visited the country, down five percent from the previous
year's total of 1.542 million.
</P>
<P>
The number of visitors from Asia during July this year totaled
27,240, a drop of 25 percent, or 9,090, compared with the same
month last year. About nine-tenths of this fall was due to a drop
in visitors from the Republic of Korea (down 8,000). However this
drop was more than offset by increases in visitors from Australia,
Britain and South Africa.
</P>
<P>
During the month of July 1998 there was a turnaround in the
migration balance, registering a net loss of 430 permanent and
long-term migrants, compared with a gain of 1,020 in July 1997.
For the whole year ending on July this year, there was a net loss
of 990 permanent and long-term migrants, compared with the net
inflow of 15,870 migrants for the previous year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
