<HEADLINE> AOC Wants Tougher Penalties for Drug Abuse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Australian Olympic Committee
(AOC) president John Coates called Monday for tougher penalties
for importing and using performance enhancing drugs.
</P>
<P>
"The level of non-medical use of anabolic steroids is now
greater than heroin and cocaine and is estimated to be two
percent of the population," said Coates in Sydney.
</P>
<P>
Coates said there was no doubt current penalties for dealing
with sports drugs were inadequate and criminal laws must be more
stringent to deter people from dealing in the drugs.
</P>
<P>
He called for legislative changes to raise the penalties for
making, importing, trafficking and use of the more serious drugs
in sport to the same level as for banned narcotics. 
