<HEADLINE> Ukraine to Keep Relations with Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine should keep traditional
relations with Russia and actively cooperate with the members of
the Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS), Chairman of the
Supreme Soviet of Ukraine Alexandr Tkachenko said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Tkachenko made the remarks when addressing a meeting
celebrating the Independence Day of Ukraine which falls on August
24.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine must live peacefully with all neighboring countries, he
said. To join European and international organizations does not
mean Ukraine should cut ties with Russia, he added.
</P>
<P>
Tkachenko also quoted President Leonid Kuchma as saying Ukraine
should actively exert its influence on the policy of the CIS
members and protect national interests.
</P>
<P>
Tkachenko pointed out that the Ukrainian people's living
standards have not improved in the seven years after
independence. During this period, he said, the country's gross
domestic product (GDP) dropped by about 62 percent, agricultural
output fell by 50 percent and half of the enterprises are losing
money.
</P>
<P>
To spur the economy, Ukraine has decided to readjust its reform
policy and make an outline for national rejuvenation, Tkachenko
said.
</P>
<P>
Ukrainian President Kuchma and Prime Minister Valery
Pustovoitenko were present at the ceremony attended by several
thousand people. 
</P>
