<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Who is Insuring China's Insurance Industry? (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dai said that the PICC RE transacts various kinds of domestic
and international reinsurance services, including compulsory
reinsurance business as entrusted by the state authorities.
</P>
<P>
According to the Insurance Law promulgated in 1995 and related
regulations issued by the State Council, the insurance companies
registered in China must reinsure 20 percent of their portfolio to
PICC RE, which accounts for more than 95 percent of the latter's
gross premium income.
</P>
<P>
Recent statistics show that in spite of the negative impact the
Asian financial crisis, the premium income the PICC RE gained
in the first half still stood at 3.35 billion yuan, up 3.38
percent on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
Up to date, the insurer has paid an indemnity totalled 369
million yuan in advance to the flood-hit areas in the Yangtze
River Valley, according to Dai.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank predicts that premium income of China's
insurance industry is expected to reach 240 billion yuan by 2000,
which also means a huge demand for reinsurance, Dai noted.
</P>
<P>
Dai disclosed that PICC RE's premium income is expected to hit
11 billion yuan this year, which will further exceed 13 billion
yuan by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
"We also plan to establish branches in Shanghai and Shenzhen."
he added.
</P>
<P>
In addition, related insiders also revealed that China's
insurance sector expects to adopt some new innovative
measures.
</P>
<P>
The PICC, for instance, will be disbanded, and its subsidiaries
of life insurance, property insurance and reinsurance, are
expected to become three independent state-run insurers.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the nation will also build up a special supervision
organization to take charge of its huge insurance market.
</P>
<P>
Local Analysts noted that the reforms will optimize the
structure of China's insurance industry, and also are beneficial
to the development of the young reinsurance undertaking.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
