signed a decree dismissing the government and naming former
premier Viktor Chernomyrdin, 60, as interim prime minister.
(Yeltsin-Cabinet-Dismissal)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Members of U.S. President Bill Clinton's Cabinet
on Sunday expressed confidence in his leadership. But his affair
with a former White House intern continued to make some prominent
Democrats uneasy, even to the point of calling for his
resignation. (US-Clinton-Democrats)
</P>
