<HEADLINE> Kenyan John Gwaco Wins Rio Half Marathon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Kenyans finished 1-2 in
the 21-kilometer half-marathon here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
John Gwaco won the title with a time of one hour, one minute,
49 seconds. His countryman James Bungei followed with a time of
1:01.55.
</P>
<P>
Brazilian Ronaldo da Costa placed third in 1:02.17.
</P>
