<HEADLINE> Italy's Serpellini Wins Tour of Portugal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Marco Serpellini of Italy won
the 2,177-kilometer Tour of Portugal as Britain's Jermy Hunt took
the 137.8km final stage between Caldas da Rainha and Lisbon on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Portugal's Orlando Rodrigues, who won the Tour in 1994 and
1995, came in second while Italian Wladimir Belli took third.
</P>
<P>
The race began in the southern Spanish city of Seville on
August 10. 
