<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kipketer Loses Again in 800 as Britain Tops Gold  Table </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan-born Dane Wilson
Kipketer suffered a stunning defeat at the European Athletics
Championships and finished last in the men's 800-meter here on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Kipketer, the world champion and world record-holder, was lea
ding the pack coming out of the last bend, but Nils Schumann of
Germany elbowed his way past Andrea Longo of Italy and Kipketer.
</P>
<P>
Kipketer, making debut in European championships, seemed to be
tiring as he was passed by all seven finalists.
</P>
<P>
Schumann, 20, European junior champion, held off Andre Bucher
of Switzerland to win the gold in 1:44.89. Bucher clocked
1:45.04, while Lukas Vydra of the Czech Republic took bronze at
1:45.23.
</P>
<P>
The final gold medal of the championships went to world triple
jump world record holder Jonathan Edwards of Britain, who soared
17.99 meters, second longest of the year after his 18.01, and a
championship record.
</P>
<P>
That gave Britain a championship-high nine gold medals and a
total of 16. Germany finished with eight golds and 23 medals
overall. Russia ended with 22 medals, including six golds.
</P>
<P>
Sonia O'Sullivan of Ireland added the 5,000m gold medal to her
10,000 title by surging ahead in the last 100 meters.
</P>
<P>
Grit Breuer got her second gold anchoring German the 4X400m to
victory in 3:23.03, and her compatriot Damian Kallabis upset
defending champion and Olympic bronze medalist Alessandro
Lambruschini of Italy to win the 3,000 steeplechase in 8:13.10.
</P>
<P>
Olympic champion Svetlana Masterkova of Russia pulled away
from world champion Carla Sacramento of Portugal on the final
turn to win the women's 1,500 in 4:11.91. Sacramento took silver
in 4:12.62 and Anita Weyerman of Switzerland won the bronze in
4:13.06.
</P>
<P>
Monica Dinescu of Romania won the women's high jump by cleari
ng 1.97 meters and Svetla Dimitrova of Bulgaria retained her
title in the 100m hurdles with 12.56. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
