<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seles Wins Fourth Canadian Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Monica Seles beat third seed
Arantxa Sanchez Vicario of Spain to win her fourth consecutive
Canadian Open title in Montreal on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The fifth seeded American took command from the start and
swept to the victory 6-3, 6-2 in one hour and 17 minutes,
collecting her first title of the year.
</P>
<P>
The matchup was a rematch of this year's French Open final
which was won by Sanchez Vicario. After a 27-month absence from
the tour following her stabbing, Seles made a dramatic return by
winning this tournament in 1995 -- and she has won it every year
since.
</P>
<P>
The French Open champion Sanchez Vicario won only 10 points on
Seles's serve and had just one break point in the entire match,
which she failed to convert. 
</P>
</TEXT>
