<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Banks Becoming Financial Advisers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Ms. Qiu, who owns a foreign
trade company in the south China city of Guangzhou, just didn't
know what to do with her increasing income, until she got a
financial adviser on her own at the individual accounts department
of the Guangzhou Branch of the China International Trust and
Investment Corporation's Industrial Bank.
</P>
<P>
She now makes a steady profit on the money she has deposited,
and can purchase shares, bonds, or investment funds.
</P>
<P>
China Business Daily recently told Ms. Qiu's story as an
example of the good results of a nationwide banking reform that
has prompted banks to improve their services in a market-oriented
reform that focuses on profit and efficiency.
</P>
<P>
CITIC Industrial Bank's Guangzhou Branch was the first to open
an individual accounts department in 1996, the daily reports, and
it can help individuals manage their money through various
investment plans. It has also enlarged its business scope by
providing individuals with housing, university study, or other
loans.
</P>
<P>
By June, it had helped customers manage 270 million yuan and
provided 300 million yuan in loans.
</P>
<P>
The Agricultural Bank of China's Guangzhou Branch, having got
the clue from CITIC Industrial, began to offer individual banking
services last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980824.0254 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South China's Guangxi Steps Up Highway Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, August 24 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region become the most efficient thoroughfare to the
sea for southwest China five years after that, when most of the
completed highways are connected with waterways and railways.
</P>
<P>
To support highway construction, the regional government has
increased investment for this purpose from the previously planned
3.73 billion yuan to five billion yuan this year, according to Li
Zhaozhuo, chairman of the regional government.
</P>
<P>
It is believed that the increased investment will be able to
generate two billion yuan in gross domestic product (GDP), provide
job opportunities to 100,000 people, and vitalize the industrial
production of cement and steel.
</P>
<P>
The Construction Bank of China Guangxi Branch recently signed
an agreement with the regional bureau of communications under
which the former will provide the latter with 6.08 billion yuan in
loans to finance the construction of communications projects in
Guangxi in the next three years. Some 1.37 billion yuan of these
loans will be provided this year.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, the autonomous region will add
2,932 kilometers of highways this year, including 203 kilometers
of expressways and 229 kilometers of graded highways.
</P>
<P>
By the year 2002, the region will have 60,000 kilometers of
highways, of which 15,000 kilometers will be newly built.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
