<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Aston Villa Beats Middlesbrough in Premier League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Aston Villa claimed their first
victory in the new English Premier league season on Sunday with a
3-1 victory over newly-promoted club Middlesbrough 3-1 at Villa
Park.
</P>
<P>
Julian Joachim fired Villa ahead from 12 meters in the sixth
minute and they should have made it two in the 39th when the same
player was hauled down by Italian defender Gianluca Festa in the
area.
</P>
<P>
However, Australian goalkeeper Mark Schwarzer dived to his
right to save Alan Thompson's penalty.
</P>
<P>
Villa, who this week sold striker Dwight Yorke to Manchester
United for 12.6 million pounds (20.51 Million U.S. dollars), were
in total command and the second goal duly arrived early in the
second half when wing back Gary Charles cut in from the right and
curled in a left-footed shot.
</P>
<P>
Dane Mikkel Beck came on for the disappointing Paul Gascoigne
after an hour and immediately pulled one back for Middlesbrough
with a sharp near post header.
</P>
<P>
But Thompson made up for his penalty failure when he lashed a
free-kick through the wall and into the net 13 minutes from time.
</P>
<P>
The victory took Villa to four points from two games, along
with six other clubs. One of them, Charlton Athletic, are the
early leaders on goal difference following their 5-0 thrashing of
Southampton on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Champions Arsenal drew 0-0 at Liverpool while Manchester
United were also involved in a goalless draw, at West Ham.
</P>
<P>
Leeds play Blackburn on Monday night. 
</P>
</TEXT>
