<HEADLINE> Corretja Beats Agassi to Win RCA Tennis Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Alex Corretja of Spain
claimed his second hardcourt title of the year today as he
rallied past American Andre Agassi in three sets to win the
745,000 U.S. dollars RCA tennis championship in Indianapolis, the
United States.
</P>
<P>
The sixth seed Corretja broke Agassi in the eighth game of the
third set and served out the 2-6, 6-2, 6-3 victory. He captured
his third ATP Tour title of the season, seventh overall and first
on American soil.
</P>
<P>
Agassi, the fifth seed, was seeking his fifth ATP Tour title
this season, which would have tied him for the 1998 lead with
Chile's Marcelo Rios. He remains one title behind Stan Smith for
12th on the all-time list with 38 victories.
</P>
<P>
Corretja, who earned his first career victory in five meetings
with Agassi, became the first Spaniard to win this event since
Jose Higueras in 1982.
</P>
<P>
A finalist at the French Open, the 24-year-old Corretja landed
his first career hardcourt title in February at the Dubai Open
and won last month's Swiss Open in Gstaad.
</P>
<P>
One day after posting his 50th match win of the year, Agassi
suffered just his third loss in 22 matches on the summer
hardcourt circuit leading up to the U.S. Open in two weeks. He
leads the ATP Tour with 44 hardcourt match wins against only
eight defeats. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980824.0259 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
