<HEADLINE> German FM Voices Concern about Russian Situation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 23 (Xinhua) -- German Foreign Minister Klaus
Kinkel Sunday expressed concern about the situation in Russia
after a sudden shakeup of the entire Russian government announced
by President Boris Yeltsin.
</P>
<P>
Apparently under the increasing pressure of a financial crisis,
Yeltsin earlier on Sunday sacked the entire cabinet of Sergei
Kiriyenko and named former Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin, who
was fired by Yeltsin just five months ago, as interim Prime
Minister.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the German ARD television network Sunday
evening, Kinkel described the situation in Russia as "not quite
confidence-promoting", but he also expressed the belief that
Chernomyrdin would be able to create confidence.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin's move came one week after the Russian government and
the central bank devalued the ruble and imposed a 90-day
moratorium on repayments of foreign debts, sending stock markets
plunging to record lows.  
</P>
</TEXT>
